30,http://www.armslist.com/posts/2462030,For Sale:  ATTENTION Mosin-Nagant Rifle Sellers IMPORTANT INFORMATION,"Dayton, Dayton, Ohio",$ 499,"Listed On: Tuesday, December 17, 2013",Rifles,American Tactical Imports                                                                                ,7.62x54R                                                                                ,Bolt Action                                                                                ,Rifle,"Just a friendly heads up.
MOST of a mosin-nagant's collect-ability comes from:
1) The type of receiver it has (round or hexagonal)
2) The Armory it was made in (stamped on the top of the receiver)
3) The stamps on the top of the receiver.
Long story short, SHOW THE TOP OF THE RECEIVER in your ads. Or else us collectors don't know if you have the most common mosin ever made, or a rare/more desirable one.
Just a PSA. Attached is an image like the kind we're looking for. It shows the style of the receiver, the stamps, and the armory stamp.

This is a 1943 Hex from the Tula armory (symbolized by the star), which is VERY rare as hex receivers had been phased out by then, thus this oddity was likely built from leftover/spare parts. But thats beside the point. Without this image/information, the seller might only be able to get $100 for the rifle. I'd pay $200-$250 for it depending on the condition of the rest of it. THIS INFORMATION IS IMPORTANT.
This will make selling it easier for you, and buying it easier for us."

The M1911A1 established the features that characterize virtually every variant produced since. It featured an extended grip safety, a clearance cut on the frame behind the trigger, a knurled and arched mainspring housing, a knurled and shortened trigger, and wider front sight.

Modern M1911s have for the most part returned to the longer trigger and flat mainspring housing, while further enlarging the ejection port and drastically modifying the grip safety to let the pistol ride lower in the hand, enhancing control by redirecting recoil forces.
